  "prompt": "How do you solve a math problem?",
  "response": "Solving a math problem involves a series of systematic steps to understand the problem, devise a plan, carry out the plan, and verify the solution. Here\u2019s a structured approach to tackling math problems:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Understand the Problem**\n   - Read the problem carefully and identify what is being asked.\n   - Highlight or underline key information, numbers, or variables.\n   - Identify any constraints or conditions given in the problem.\n   - Rewrite the problem in your own words to ensure comprehension.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Plan the Solution**\n   - Determine what type of problem it is (algebraic, geometric, calculus, etc.).\n   - Recall relevant formulas, theorems, or strategies that apply to the problem.\n   - Break the problem into smaller, manageable steps.\n   - Decide on the approach or method to solve the problem (e.g., substitution, elimination, drawing a diagram).\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Carry Out the Plan**\n   - Execute the steps you outlined, showing all your work.\n   - Perform calculations carefully, checking for errors as you go.\n   - If you encounter a roadblock, revisit your plan and try an alternative approach.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Verify the Solution**\n   - Check your answer to ensure it makes sense in the context of the problem.\n   - Substitute your solution back into the original problem to confirm its validity.\n   - Look for alternative methods to solve the problem and see if they yield the same result.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Reflect and Learn**\n   - Analyze the problem-solving process to identify what worked well and what didn\u2019t.\n   - Consider how you can apply this process to similar problems in the future.\n\n---\n\n### Tips for Success:\n   - Practice regularly to build familiarity with different types of problems.\n   - Stay organized and write clearly to avoid mistakes.\n   - Ask for help or consult resources (textbooks, online tutorials) if you\u2019re stuck.\n   - Be patient and persistent\u2014math problem-solving often requires trial and error.\n\nBy following these steps and practicing consistently, you\u2019ll improve your ability to solve math problems effectively.",
